Also, the following was taken from a post on CNN.com:<br>
<br>
&quot;1) What happened to make the plane crash in Pennsylvania? Did it get shot down? Isn't it a little too ironic that this specific crash had little coverage? <br>
<br>
2) Lady Liberty watched the whole day unfold. But, everyone around the world show notice that she is still carrying the torch proclaiming what America is all about. <br>
<br>
3) A, B, and C are the first three letters of the alphabet. Airplane crashes, Biological weapons, and Chemical weapons are three major threats to the USA. I hope they don't hurt us in that order. <br>
<br>
4) The bidding and selling activity on eBay items with the search words &quot;World Trade Center&quot; jumped tremendously within hours of the first reports of the tragedy. Nearly all the items listed were removed by eBay within 30 minutes to an hour. <br>
<br>
5) I would not be very surprised to wake up tomorrow and learn that Bin Laden has been assassinated. <br>
<br>
6) Do the insurance policies of the companies located in the World Trade Center cover attacks such as this? Is this considered an Act of War? I would not want to have equity in any insurance company tied into the WTC. <br>
<br>
7) Is the worst behind us? Or is the worst yet to come? What could be next? In Chicago today, I felt VERY vulnerable being so close to the Sears Tower. During my entire commute while transfixed by the radio, I kept one eye on the landmark proclaiming the nation's best skyline. <br>
<br>
8. Is there any irony in today's date 9-11? Is there any irony in that one of the flight numbers was #11?&quot;<br>
<br>
