<br>
At least here in America you have the choice to follow a certain organized religion or not as your own beliefs dictate.<br>
<br>
To answer your question...<br>
<br>
I think people that are part of organized religions find comfort and support from their fellow members during the many trials that this life visits upon everyone and this is the main reason they choose to join one religion or another. It's not fun to cry alone. You can also share the many joys of faith and happy times in your life with those around you. In short...it's nice to be part of a group of people with like-minded faith and beliefs.<br>
