That being said, my purpose at the moment is try to make sense of things. As I said, the original questions 1-8, weren't mine, they were posted by someone on the CNN.com forums, but I thought they had a lot of merit and was curious to see how you guys would answer them. As it is, I'm still a little confused on a few points, most of which were brought up here. For example: if they were only armed with knives and boxcutters, wouldn't people try and overpower them? How many terrorists were on board? 1? 2? 20? I wish we had more information, but the details of what went on are sketchy at best. I can't even begin to fathom what must have been going through people's minds as the plane was being hijacked, and how those people must have felt being faced with the possiblity of death.<br>
